text: @ScottWapnerCNBC Re $NFLX bull: Netflix reported weak second quarter subscriber growth in Q2 (just 1.5 million new adds) and revenue growth dropped below 20% for the first time in a decade. In North America, the company actually lost a net 430,000 subscribers. @HalftimeReport

Bull markets are borne out of bad news March 2020) and bear markets/corrections are borne out of good news. Markets move more on rate of change than absolute change. See "Is FAANG Losing Its Flavor" @ScottWapnerCNBC @HalftimeReport realmoney.thestreet.com/doug…

Respectfully, stating "known knowns" (earnings rising, economy prospering, EPS beating forecasts EPS) tells us nothing about where the market is heading.... it tells us where we have been. @HalftimeReport @scottwapner

That, too is unfair and inaccurate. All I am tweeting is that there is a responsibility to memorialize and report results of trade recommendations (esp. in options) to viewers - so that they, in turn, can evaluate the value added and merit of the ideas. @ScottWapnerCNBC

This is not about Najarian who by all accounts is a good guy. But, all @cnbc should do is memorialize the recommendations of their panelists - so viewers can figure out who to listen to! Hire an intern to tabulate the results - its that easy, Judge. @ScottWapnerCNBC

This AM $CLX is down -$20/share of a huge miss to expectations. Am I the only one that calls out this "unusual call activity" BS? The failure to document the performance of directional call option ideas is mind boggling to me. @SquawkCNBC @ScottWapnerCNBC @jimcramer @tomkeene
